	"system": {
		"description": {
			"value": "<p><em>Holding a piece of wire meant to hold eggs to dip them in paint, you gesture as if lifting a creature or object from afar, calling a spirit of air. The creature or object lifts into the air and gains the ability to float above the ground.</em></p><p><strong>Buff</strong></p><p>The spell can levitate a willing creature or object that weighs up to 500 pounds.</p><ul><li><p>Target immediately rises up to 20 ft. into the air (your choice).</p></li><li><p>Target gains a fly speed of 20 ft. and can hover.</p></li><li><p><strong>Concentration:</strong> Once per turn, you can use your action to move the levitated target up to 20 ft., but never higher than 20 ft. off the ground.</p></li></ul><p><strong>Upcasting:</strong> Target one additional creature for each spell level above 2nd.</p>",
			"chat": ""
		},
